   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <supplied reason="lost">Ἀφρο</supplied>διτί  
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>To Aphrodite.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The mosaic fragment depicts an Eros riding a dolphin amidst marine life and (above to the left) the end of the name 'Aphrodite' in the dative case, indicating a dedication to her; the left edge of the fragment seems to preserve the right edge of a medallion, perhaps depicting a bust of the goddess. The mosaic is said to have come from Rome and may be presumed to have originated in one of the suburban villas in the area; style and content suggest a date in the third century CE.</p>
         </div>
